---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Advanced Online docs"
  description="Managed Thumbrella hosting with global delivery, higher limits, and support."
>
  <Section
    eyebrow="advanced online"
    title="Managed hosting with global delivery and support"
    lede="When the free hosted tier is not enough, move to a managed plan and get global CDN coverage, higher throughput limits, SLA guarantees, and the full API surface."
  >
    <ol>
      <li>Upgrade from the free tier in the account dashboard.</li>
      <li>Choose the plan that fits your request volume and support needs.</li>
      <li>Your existing integration keeps working with no endpoint changes.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      Plans scale from individual developers to teams running production media pipelines at volume.
      All paid plans include priority support, higher rate limits, and access to beta features before
      they land in the free tier.
    </p>
  </Section>
</MainLayout>
